<dl id="n35287a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n35" href="#n35287a">N35 (VI.B.24)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n35all.htm#n35287a"> 287(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 7 fora / 7 hills</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[<i>History, Architecture and Antiquities</i>.&mdash;]</font> The street along the ridge formed the principal thoroughfare, and was named the Mes&eacute; (<i>Meon</i>), because it ran through the middle of t he city. <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> The Mes&eacute; linked together the great fora of the city,&mdash;the Augustaion on the south of St Sophia, the forum of Constantine on the summit of the 2nd hill, <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> the forum of Theodosius II. on the summit of the 7th hill. <small> &ldquo;CONSTANTINOPLE&rdquo; <cite a>Encyclopaedia Britannica</cite></a>, 11th edit. (1911) 5</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
